  "summary": "event-metrics-q3x7 ships postinstall beacon scripts that exfiltrate host data over HTTP",
  "details": "On install, package.json's postinstall hook runs node run.js, which loads beacon scripts (beacon19.js, beacon_linux.js) that combine child_process, os, and http modules to gather host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.platform()) and transmit them via http.request POST/GET calls. The package's only declared install-time effect is to execute these beacon scripts that pair OS/host enumeration with outbound HTTP requests — the canonical install-time exfiltration shape, with no legitimate library functionality declared.",
